722635f-b.text:
(1)
330 Pleasant Ave., east side, between 117th and 118th Streets. This building is an old house which has been used for a dosen or more years as a Settlement House (The Neighborhood House), of the Church Extension Committee of the Presbytery of New York
and is now being given up.
July 1S, 1927.
P. L. Sperr.
(2)
The same, five years later.
1932.
J. Clarenoe Davies Collection, Museum of the City of New York.
Negative No. 252.

715152f-b.text:
East 117th Street, west from Pleasant Avenue, showing pavement conditions on the north side of this street. At the left midground is the institutional building that houses P. 3. No. 85. This is at the S. W. corner of First Avenue. View E shows details of the sidewalk at the N.E. corner at that Avenue. The Second Avenue "El" station
appears in the background of both views.
May 4, 1937
No's. 1-2
W. ". A., photo
Five Boroughs Project
